CONDITIONAL STATEMENTS:
**********************

. To make the set of instructions execute only when the given condition is true
. Used to decide whether the code has to be executed or skip based on the given condition 
. skip the code based on evaluation
. Executes in a sequence (line by line)

BLOCK OF CODE: Set of instructions
*************
* Executes when the specific condition is true


CONDITION : An expression that evaluates the result(True or False)
*********  
            EX: console.log(5>6)

METHODS :
********
. if
. if-else
. else if
. switch
. Ternary operator


If:   - only one possible condition
***
. if the condition is true it executes other wise it will skip

syntax :
*******

if(condition){
block of code
}

executes only the block of code (condition) is true

EXAMPLE: 1
*******
<script>
        let a=4
        let b=5
        if (a<b){
            document.write("hello world")
        }
 </script>

// OUTPUT : "hello world"



EXAMPLE : 2
********
<script>
        let a=4
        let b=5
        if (a<b){
            document.write("hello world","<br>")
        }
        document.write("hello harshitha")
    </script>

//OUTPUT:

     hello world
     hello harshitha



EXAMPLE: 3
********
<script>
        let a=4
        let b=5
        if (a>b){
            document.write("hello world","<br>")
        }
        document.write("hello harshitha","<br>")
    </script>


// OUTPUT :hello harshitha



 IF-ELSE : - if condition not satisfies print the else block
***********

EXAMPLE 1:
**********

<script>
        let a=4
        let b=5
        if (a>b){
            document.write("hello world","<br>")
        }else{
            document.write("Hi Manvitha","<br>")

        }
        document.write("Hi Harshitha")
    </script>

// OUTPUT :

Hi Manvitha
Hi Harshitha


EXAMPLE 2 :
**********

<script>
        let age=prompt("Enter your age?")
        let name=prompt("Enter your name?")
        if(age<18){
            alert(name+ "you are to young to marry")
        }else if(age>35){
            alert(name+ "you are to old to marry")
        }else{
            alert(name+ "perfect age to marry")
        }

// OUTPUT :

"Enter your age" :20
"Enter your name" : G.Harshitha
G.Harshitha perfect age to marry



Example 2:
*********

<script>
        let a=prompt("Enter your a score: ")
        let b=prompt("Enter your b score: ")
        let c=a+b
        if((a>300 || b>300) && (c<500)){
            alert(" valid to team up")
        }else{
            alert(" not valid to team up")
        }
    </script>

// OUTPUT : 

Enter your a score: 302
Enter your b score: 100
not valid to team up


